    <item>
      <title>Re: Adventure stone question.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=247610#M247610</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
richardya wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I never got my adventure stone. Rog Half Elf Lvl 60. Karana.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;I have done LDON's&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;1)Where do I get it?&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;2)Will I get credit for LDON's I have done or will I have to redo them?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The Adventurures Stone is just an aug that allows you to travel between LDoN camps.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; When everything is working, you walk in to your home city, and you get some message about the Wayfarers.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Then you're told who to speak to, and there's lots of dialog.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; You need to recall all of this dialog, because when you go to the Wayfarer camp you are directed to, you are asked a bunch of questions and need to know the correct answers (no [bracket] responses here).&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;You give all the right answers, you receive an aug, and once you place the aug in a slot, you can now talk to the Magus at each camp to be teleported to any of the other camps.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; There's also a Magus in the Guild Lobby.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Oh... and this have no effect either way on credit for LDoN missions.&amp;nbsp; You can do them, and get credit, with or without the aug.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
